        "Heading_size": "h2",
        "Heading_color": "#f8f2e6",
        "title": "It Started Almost A Century Ago",
        "video-sec-content-txt-1": "<p>In 1928, South Africa took note when a young, unknown rugby player, Albertus Viljoen van der Merwe – “Alvi” to his friends – made history by scoring the first try in history against the All Blacks on African soil. </p><p>Today, we make history with award-winning wines recognised by South Africa and the world. Our 221 Range is named after Oupa Alvi, who had a legendary rugby career as the 221st player for the Springboks.</p>",
        "button-txt": "221 Range",
        "button_link": "shopify://collections/221-range",
